Anti-Catholicism has always been the pornography of the Puritan. Whereas
the anti-Masons had envisaged drinking bouts and had entertained themselves
with sado-masochistic fantasies about the actual enforcement of grisly
Masonic oaths, the anti-Catholics invented an immense lore about libertine
priests, the confessional as an opportunity for seduction, licentious
convents and monasteries.
    --Richard Hofstadter, "The Paranoid Style in American Politics" (1964)
